strategy_1_exclusion.name: Exclusion Strategy
strategy_1_exclusion.description: Exclude products without valid drive links from JSON files

implementation.criteria: Only include products with valid Google Drive links

pros: Ensures all products have supporting documentation

strategy_2_placeholder.name: Placeholder Strategy
strategy_2_placeholder.description: Include products with placeholder drive links and enhancement flags

implementation.criteria: Include all products with quality flags
implementation.enhancement_queue: Track products needing drive link updates

cons: May confuse users with incomplete data

strategy_3_alternative_sourcing.name: Alternative Sourcing Strategy
strategy_3_alternative_sourcing.description: Source alternative documentation for products without drive links

implementation.sources: Manufacturer websites, product databases, specifications sheets
implementation.validation: Verify accuracy and completeness of sourced data

cons: Variable data quality from different sources

strategy_4_tiered_approach.name: Tiered Quality Approach
strategy_4_tiered_approach.description: Implement quality tiers based on drive link availability
strategy_4_tiered_approach.approach: Multi-tier system with clear quality indicators

implementation.tier_1: Products with valid drive links (premium tier)
implementation.tier_2: Products with detailed specifications but no links (standard tier)
implementation.tier_3: Products with basic information only (basic tier)
implementation.metadata: Clear tier indicators in product data

pros: Balanced approach to quality and completeness
